The paper deals with analyzing spatial redundancy in natural images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The statistical framework and testing methodology presented in the paper involve concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The applications of the framework include denoising and texture ranking, which are also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
